# isNegative

- _isNegative(aNumber)_

Answers `true` if _aNumber_ is negative, else `false`.

```
>>> 1.isNegative
false

>>> -1.isNegative
true
```

Threads over lists:

```
>>> [1.6, 3/4, pi, 0, -5, (10 ^ 5).sin].isNegative
[false false false false true false]
```

